name: AnyInfectionPriorToAnesthesiaConceptsICD9CM
title: Any Infection Prior to Anesthesia Concepts ICD9CM
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values identifies patients who have preoperative documentation of an infection.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who have preoperative documentation of an infection.  Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the Diagnosis category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Only use codes which represent select infections. Codes used are to be ICD9CM codes only.),(Exclusion Criteria: Exclude codes that do not meet the inclusion criteria.  These include codes for fungal infections, viral infections and infections that are not documented as current or active.)
